<Link id="l00056" /><CodeLine lineNumber="56"><span class="doxyHighlightComment"> &#42;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00057" /><CodeLine lineNumber="57"><span class="doxyHighlightComment"> &#42; This is intended to simplify transitions for existing MCJIT clients. The</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00058" /><CodeLine lineNumber="58"><span class="doxyHighlightComment"> &#42; callbacks used are similar (but not identical) to the callbacks for</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00059" /><CodeLine lineNumber="59"><span class="doxyHighlightComment"> &#42; LLVMCreateSimpleMCJITMemoryManager: Unlike MCJIT, RTDyldObjectLinkingLayer</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00060" /><CodeLine lineNumber="60"><span class="doxyHighlightComment"> &#42; will create a new memory manager for each object linked by calling the given</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00061" /><CodeLine lineNumber="61"><span class="doxyHighlightComment"> &#42; CreateContext callback. This allows for code removal by destroying each</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00062" /><CodeLine lineNumber="62"><span class="doxyHighlightComment"> &#42; allocator individually. Every allocator will be destroyed (if it has not been</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00063" /><CodeLine lineNumber="63"><span class="doxyHighlightComment"> &#42; already) at RTDyldObjectLinkingLayer destruction time, and the</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00064" /><CodeLine lineNumber="64"><span class="doxyHighlightComment"> &#42; NotifyTerminating callback will be called to indicate that no further</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00065" /><CodeLine lineNumber="65"><span class="doxyHighlightComment"> &#42; allocation contexts will be created.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00066" /><CodeLine lineNumber="66"><span class="doxyHighlightComment"> &#42;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00067" /><CodeLine lineNumber="67"><span class="doxyHighlightComment"> &#42; To implement MCJIT-like behavior clients can implement CreateContext,</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00068" /><CodeLine lineNumber="68"><span class="doxyHighlightComment"> &#42; NotifyTerminating, and Destroy as:</span></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00071" /><CodeLine lineNumber="71"><span class="doxyHighlightComment"> &#42;   void NotifyTerminating(void &#42;CtxCtx) &#123; MyOriginalDestroy(CtxCtx); &#125;</span></CodeLine>
